          <div class="head-content-h">
            <h2>Types of Wolf Stoves We Service</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-container">
          <div class="right-content">
            <p>We repair all Wolf stove configurations, including:</p>
            <ul>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2 no-bullet" style="padding-left: 0 !important;" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Gas Stoves</strong> – Signature dual-stacked sealed burners (e.g., GR304, GR366)</li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2 no-bullet" style="padding-left: 0 !important;" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Electric Stoves</strong> – Smooth-top radiant models</li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2 no-bullet" style="padding-left: 0 !important;" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Dual-Fuel Ranges</strong> – Gas cooktop with electric convection oven (e.g., DF304, DF484)</li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2 no-bullet" style="padding-left: 0 !important;" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Induction Cooktops</strong> – Precision-controlled heat (e.g., CI304C/B, CI365C/B)</li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2 no-bullet" style="padding-left: 0 !important;" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Slide-In & Freestanding Ranges</strong> – For both custom and standard kitchen installations</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="page-container" id="anchor-3">
        <div class="header-container">
          <div class="head-content-h">
